FBIS4-13746 "drnes078_v_94001" FBIS-NES-94-078 Daily Report 21 Apr 1994 Pakistan Foreign Minister Denies U.S. Seeking Military Bases Foreign Minister Denies U.S. Seeking Military Bases BK2104151094 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 1400 GMT 21 Apr 94 BK2104151094 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network Urdu BFN [Text] The National Assembly was informed today that the government has again raised with the French Government the issue of the supply of the nuclear power plant to Pakistan. Foreign Minister Sardar Asif Ahmad Ali, in a written reply to a question, described as false the rumors that the United States has sought Pakistan's permission for establishing military bases. He said there is no question whatsoever of any commitment from Pakistan's side to the United States to set up military bases here. In reply to a question by Mian Abdul Waheed, the foreign minister said spares of the defense equipment, including the F-16's, are being purchased from the United States on commercial basis due to the Pressler Amendment.
